body:
Please fill in this template.

- [x] Use a meaningful title for the pull request. Include the name of the package modified.
- [x] Test the change in your own code. (Compile and run.)
- [x] Follow the advice from the [readme](https://github.com/DefinitelyTyped/DefinitelyTyped/blob/master/README.md#make-a-pull-request).

http://blog.jquery.com/2014/01/24/jquery-1-11-and-2-1-released/
http://blog.jquery.com/2016/01/08/jquery-2-2-and-1-12-released/
http://blog.jquery.com/2016/06/09/jquery-3-0-final-released/
http://blog.jquery.com/2016/07/07/jquery-3-1-0-released-no-more-silent-errors/
http://blog.jquery.com/2017/03/16/jquery-3-2-0-is-out/
- [x] Increase the version number in the header if appropriate.
- [x] If you are making substantial changes, consider adding a `tslint.json` containing `{ "extends": "dtslint/dt.json" }`.

### Summary
This is a rewrite of the jQuery type definitions. My goals were to increase accuracy, coverage, and align terminology/names with how they're presented in jQuery docs. I tried to maintain backwards-compatibility with the old type definitions when possible. This also makes use of TypeScript 2.1, 2.2, and 2.3 features. As a result, I had to tag a lot of dependents (this look a **long** time).

- Fixes #15733
- Fixes #11115
- Closes #426 (this was already fixed in the old definitions)
- Closes #16620 (fixed for v2 in #16621)
- Fixes the following _only_ for v3
  - Fixes #14515
  - Fixes #13017
  - Fixes #7042
  - Fixes #5596
  - Fixes #2146
  - Fixes #2012
  - Fixes #1445

### File structure
Old typings were copied to both `v2` **and** `v1` since they represented 2.0 and 1.10 respectively.
- `test/example-tests.ts` contains tests generated from examples in docs
- `test/longdesc-tests.ts` contains tests generated from code snippets in descriptions in docs
- `jquery-tests.ts` covers TypeScript-specific features and parts not covered by the other tests

### Changes
- Dropped portions of the API that were removed in 3.0
- `JQuery` now declares `Iterable` as a base type so `for...of` is now possible
- `JQuery` is now generic, allowing for the possibility of working with other DOMs
  - jQuery can work with SVG, although it's officially unsupported
- The export is now correctly defined as a factory function
- More overloads should be covered along with a few missing methods
- Typed `this` in callbacks
- Matched jQuery's terminology where reasonable
  - For example, `JQueryEventObject` is now `JQuery.Event`

### Issues and potential bugs
- The following overloads have to be kept separated. If they're unified, `any` seems to 'win' and the function becomes untyped. 
  - [source](https://github.com/leonard-thieu/DefinitelyTyped/blob/6a556da667ad5eac21c171c50d26bd81c75a99a5/types/jquery/index.d.ts#L1671)
  - [test](https://github.com/leonard-thieu/DefinitelyTyped/blob/6a556da667ad5eac21c171c50d26bd81c75a99a5/types/jquery/test/longdesc-tests.ts#L2100)
```typescript
prop(propertyName: string, value: (this: TElement, index: number, oldPropertyValue: any) => any): this;
prop(propertyName: string, value: any): this;
```
- `Deferred.promise(object)` mixes an `object` with a `Promise`, however, the intersected type doesn't seem to survive chaining even when the method returns `this`.
  - [source](https://github.com/leonard-thieu/DefinitelyTyped/blob/6a556da667ad5eac21c171c50d26bd81c75a99a5/types/jquery/index.d.ts#L1652)
  - [test](https://github.com/leonard-thieu/DefinitelyTyped/blob/6a556da667ad5eac21c171c50d26bd81c75a99a5/types/jquery/test/example-tests.ts#L1217)
```typescript
promise<TTarget extends object>(target: TTarget): JQuery.Promise<TResolve> & TTarget;
```
- [`AjaxSettings<TContext>`](https://github.com/leonard-thieu/DefinitelyTyped/blob/6a556da667ad5eac21c171c50d26bd81c75a99a5/types/jquery/index.d.ts#L3279) can't set its type argument to itself. `this` in callbacks on `AjaxSettings` is supposed to be the settings object itself unless [`context`](https://github.com/leonard-thieu/DefinitelyTyped/blob/6a556da667ad5eac21c171c50d26bd81c75a99a5/types/jquery/index.d.ts#L3337) is defined. If `TContext` is set to `AjaxSettings`, it results in a compiler crash. I'm not sure how to properly model this relationship.
- Content adding methods on `JQuery` ([`after`](https://github.com/leonard-thieu/DefinitelyTyped/blob/6a556da667ad5eac21c171c50d26bd81c75a99a5/types/jquery/index.d.ts#L88), [`append`](https://github.com/leonard-thieu/DefinitelyTyped/blob/6a556da667ad5eac21c171c50d26bd81c75a99a5/types/jquery/index.d.ts#L197), [`before`](https://github.com/leonard-thieu/DefinitelyTyped/blob/6a556da667ad5eac21c171c50d26bd81c75a99a5/types/jquery/index.d.ts#L255), [`prepend`](https://github.com/leonard-thieu/DefinitelyTyped/blob/6a556da667ad5eac21c171c50d26bd81c75a99a5/types/jquery/index.d.ts#L1584)) are supposed to be called with at least 1 argument. Declaring it like the following hurts usability with the spread operator though. Is there a decent way to represent it?
```typescript
append(content: JQuery.htmlString | JQuery.TypeOrArray<Element | Text> | JQuery,
       ...contents: Array<JQuery.htmlString | JQuery.TypeOrArray<Element | Text> | JQuery>): this;
```
- Variadic types aren't currently available but would help a lot.

Since this is a large amount of changes, I appreciate _anyone_ who takes the time to review this PR.

<sub>On a side note, I tried to declare `jQuery` as a class given that `jQuery` is really a constructor function but that didn't pan out. I got everything working except for plugins (which some people may find to be a big deal). I couldn't figure out why `jQuery` interfaces were refusing to merge. If anyone wants to take a crack at it, my best attempt can be found at https://github.com/leonard-thieu/DefinitelyTyped/tree/jquery-rewrite/types/jquery.</sub>
